  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/mild-and-creamy-smoky-fish-curry/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a wide-based pan (preferably non-stick)&nbsp;with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a low heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 8-10 min or until softened</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/mild-and-creamy-smoky-fish-curry/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>basmati rice</strong>, <strong>sultanas</strong> and 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span><strong> cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked &ndash; this is your <strong>sultana rice</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/mild-and-creamy-smoky-fish-curry/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve&nbsp;1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span>&nbsp;<strong>vegetable stock cube</strong> in 250ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> of <strong>boiled water</strong></p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\r\n<p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>ginger</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once the<strong> onions</strong> have softened, add the <strong>garam masala</strong>, <strong>korma curry powder</strong>, <strong>chopped ginger</strong> and <strong>garlic</strong>&nbsp;and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/mild-and-creamy-smoky-fish-curry/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>vegetable stock</strong> and cook for 3-5 min or until the liquid has reduced slightly</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, cut the <strong>smoked basa fillets</strong> into rough bite-sized pieces&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once slightly reduced, add the <strong>ground almonds</strong> and <strong>chopped smoked basa</strong> to the pan with a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cook, covered, for 4-5 min or until the <strong>basa</strong> is fully cooked&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/mild-and-creamy-smoky-fish-curry/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>coriander</strong>&nbsp;roughly (including the stalks)</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/mild-and-creamy-smoky-fish-curry/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the <strong>basa</strong> is cooked through,&nbsp;add the <strong>natural</strong>&nbsp;<strong>yoghurt</strong> and cook for a further 1 min, season with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong>&nbsp;&ndash; this is your <strong>smoky</strong>&nbsp;<strong>fish curry</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/mild-and-creamy-smoky-fish-curry/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>smoky fish curry</strong> with the&nbsp;<strong>sultana rice</strong> to the side</p>\r\n<p>Garnish with the<strong> chopped&nbsp;coriander</strong></p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
